  "prompt": "Why doesn't Obama release his academic records? Why are people making detailed statements about Obama's academic record if the information has not been made public in documents that can be verified?",
  "response": "The release of academic records for any individual, including public figures, is generally a matter of personal privacy. Barack Obama, like many other public figures, has chosen not to release his academic records. This is not unusual, as academic records are protected under privacy laws such as the Family Educational Rights and Privacy Act (FERPA), and it is up to the individual whether to make them public.\n\nPeople may still make detailed statements about Obama's academic record based on personal accounts, interviews, or other indirect sources. However, unless such information is corroborated by the release of official documents, these statements should be taken cautiously, as they may rely on anecdotal evidence or secondhand information.\n\nDiscussions about Obama's academic records often arise from political motivations or intense public interest in his background and career. While some people might doubt or question why he hasn't released these records, others argue that there's little precedent or necessity for public figures to disclose their academic history in detail, as their professional achievements and public service tend to be more relevant.",
